<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146453>
    dc:description "FIGURE 52. A–E. Edessa (E.) magnifica (Pirán, 1958) comb. n.: A, dorsal surface of the holotype; B, genital plates of the holotype in ventral view; C, holotype labels; D–E, dorsal and ventral surface. Scale= 1 mm for genitalia and 5 mm for the body. The photos were taken by Pablo R. Mulieri and Gastón E. Zubarán." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146453/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146455>
    dc:description "FIGURE 53. A–F. Edessa (E.) magnifica (Pirán, 1958) comb. n.: A–E, pygophore in dorsal, dorsolateral, ventral, posterior and posterolateral views, respectively; F, metasternal process. Scale= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146455/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146497>
    dc:description "FIGURE 73. Distribution map of the species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146497/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146560>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A–G. Edessa (E.) atricornis sp. n.: A–E, pygophore in dorsal, dorsolateral, ventral, posterior and posterolateral views, respectively; F, genital plates; G, metasternal process. mt8—mediotergite VIII. Scale= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146560/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146397>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. A–G. Edessa (E.) immaculata sp. n.: A–E, pygophore in dorsal, dorsolateral, ventral, posterior and posterolateral views, respectively; F, genital plates; G, metasternal process. Scale= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146397/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

